three_laps <- mario_kart %>% 
  filter(type == "Three Lap")

Datasets with and without the Rainbow Road track:

three_without_rainbow <- three_laps %>% 
  filter(track != "Rainbow Road")

three_only_rainbow <- three_laps %>% 
  filter(track == "Rainbow Road")

Question 2

Summary statistics for races at Rainbow Road and all other tracks

rainbow_summary <- three_only_rainbow %>% 
  summarize(mean = mean(time), std_dev = sd(time))

rainbow_summary
## # A tibble: 1  2
##    mean std_dev
##   <dbl>   <dbl>
## 1  276.    91.8
all_other_summary <- three_without_rainbow %>% 
  summarize(mean = mean(time), std_dev = sd(time))

all_other_summary
## # A tibble: 1  2
##    mean std_dev
##   <dbl>   <dbl>
## 1  114.    53.0

The average time to complete a race is considerably longer on Rainbow Road that on every other track. That the standard deviation for Rainbow Road is larger than that of all others (grouped together) suggests that the difference in means isnt due to variability in completion times on other tracks but that Rainbow Road is just longer and/or harder to finish.

Question 2

Pivoting data into tidy format

nfl_salary_tidy <- nfl_salary %>% 
  pivot_longer(names_to = "position", # column names to position
               values_to = "salary", 
               cols = -year) # want to keep year the same
